<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: DU PONT PICKS WOOLARD AS ITS NEW CHAIRMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Edgar S. Woolard Jr. has been named chairman and chief executive of Du Pont Co. 
Woolard succeeds Richard E. Heckert, who is retiring. Heckert becomes chairman 
of the finance committee, succeeding Edward G. Jefferson. 
</P>
<P>
Elwood P. Blanchard continues as vice chairman and becomes a member of the 
finance committee. 
</P>
<P>
Woolard, 55, also was appointed chairman of the policy-making executive 
committee at the Wilmington, Del., company. He was elected vice chairman in 
1985 and president and chief operating officer in 1987. 
</P>
</TEXT>
