<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
From the High-Definition Television File: A high-definition television 
demonstration using "Gone With the Wind" is being shown at the National Assn. 
of Broadcasters convention in Las Vegas by Turner Entertainment Co. and Rank 
Cintel. Rank Cintel is the developer and manufacturer of a new machine, called 
the MKIII HD (1125/60) flying spot telecine, that will make film-to-tape 
transfer. HDTV provides an image quality more than twice as detailed as today's 
video standard. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
