<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Good Morgan: Veteran comedian Pat Buttram will start delivering a few minutes 
of humorous commentary on Robert W. Morgan's morning KMPC radio program 
beginning Monday. "I finally got tired of all the deejays in the morning 
quoting my jokes. . . . I decided to start getting paid for all those jokes," 
Buttram said Wednesday. Morgan's 5:30-9 a.m. show will include the daily 
feature "Pat Buttram on Location" during which Buttram will call in from around 
the country and comment on the day's news events or other topical material. 
"It'll be kind of on-the-scene commentary about whatever is going on," said 
Buttram, 70, who got his start in radio in 1934. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Buttram 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
