ABANDONED EXOTIC FISH FOUL MICHIGAN WATERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
YPSILANTI, Mich. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fisherman was astonished when the fish he hooked in the Huron River turned 
out to be a piranha. 
</P>
<P>
"I thought it was a bluegill," George Kearney said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Ned Fogle, of the State Department of Natural Resources' fisheries 
division, said dumping of tropical fish in Michigan waters is increasing as 
aquarium owners become bored with their exotic fish. 
</P>
