<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRAYERS FOR RAINFALL PAY OFF IN BANGLADESH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DHAKA, Bangladesh 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rain fell Wednesday in parts of Bangladesh after people across the country 
prayed for an end to a drought that threatens to destroy almost 50% of the rice 
crop. 
</P>
<P>
Hours after the prayers by more than 75,000 Muslims, led by President Hussain 
Mohammed Ershad, light rain fell in the capital of Dhaka and three other 
districts, the weather bureau said. 
</P>
<P>
But forecasters say there will probably be no respite from the drought for 
another two weeks, and a hot spell will aggravate the situation in the coming 
days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
