<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: BALDWIN PARK; 
</P>
<P>
HOUSING DIRECTOR RESIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Friday will be John Hemer's last day as director of Housing and Economic 
Development. 
</P>
<P>
Hemer, 44, said he is leaving to become director of real estate for the Los 
Angeles Redevelopment Agency. 
</P>
<P>
"The opportunity came up," Hemer said. "In Baldwin Park I had completed all the 
goals I had set when I came here. 
</P>
<P>
He said during his 7 1/2 years, he has helped add 400 apartments and 
condominiums and more than 1 million square feet of retail and industrial 
space. 
</P>
<P>
At the Los Angeles Redevelopment Agency, Hemer will oversee a staff of 30, more 
than double the number he has been supervising. He will specialize in land 
appraisals, acquisitions and sales. 
</P>
<P>
Hemer, who handled redevelopment projects for Inglewood and Santa Monica before 
coming to Baldwin Park in 1981, said he is proud of his role in completing the 
city's Puente-Merced project, which features a Vons supermarket and Hilton 
hotel. 
</P>
