<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CANE KNOCKS CONNORS OUT EARLY, 7-6, 6-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jimmy Connors' comeback in the $607,500 Monte Carlo Open was a short one. 
</P>
<P>
The fifth-seeded Connors, making his first appearance in the tournament in 
eight years, was eliminated in the second round Wednesday by Paolo Cane of 
Italy, 7-6 (7-5), 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
"I haven't played on clay courts in two years," Connors said. "I'll take my 
beatings on clay for something down the road. I'm over here for 14 weeks." 
</P>
<P>
In two other surprises, Guy Forget of France upset seventh-seeded Emilio 
Sanchez of Spain, 6-7 (2-7), 6-4, 6-1, and Carl Uwe Steeb of West Germany 
ousted No. 12 Andrei Chesnokov of the Soviet Union, 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Chris Evert needed only 1 hour 8 minutes to beat South Africa's 
Karen Schimper, 6-1, 6-2, in the first round of a Virginia Slims tournament at 
Houston. 
</P>
<P>
Third-seeded Lori McNeil overcame Laxmi Poruri, 7-6 (7-5), 6-2, in the second 
round. 
</P>
<P>
In other second-round matches, seventh-seeded Gretchen Magers defeated Katrina 
Adams, 6-4, 6-2 and Monica Seles defeated eighth-seeded Amy Frazier, 5-7, 6-4, 
6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Hu Na defeated Maureen Drake, 6-2, 7-6, in another first-round match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
