<HEADLINE>
<P>
STANFORD TOPS SPIKER MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN DROOZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Western Intercollegiate Volleyball Assn. regional selection tournament will 
be played today and Saturday at Loyola Marymount. The single-elimination 
tourney will determine an at-large entry to the men's NCAA championships. 
</P>
<P>
Tonight's match-ups pit Stanford against USC at 6 and Hawaii vs. UC Santa 
Barbara at 8. The championship will be decided at 7:30 p.m. Saturday. The 
winner will join the regular-season conference champion, UCLA, in the NCAA 
final four, along with two teams from Eastern and Midwest regions. Stanford, 
which tied UCLA in the conference standings but lost a coin flip for the title, 
is the tourney's top seed. 
</P>
<P>
The WIVA is the nation's dominant volleyball conference, having produced every 
NCAA champion since a final four was started 19 years ago. The WIVA produced 27 
of the 30 members of the 1984 and 1988 U.S. Olympic teams. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets are available through Ticketron outlets or at the Loyola ticket office. 
Seats are $10, $7 and $5 each night. ALAN DROOZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA042789-0120 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 49544 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 27, 1989, Thursday, South Bay Edition 
</P>
