<P>
EARNINGS: SAN DIEGO COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mitek Systems, a manufacturer of laser printers and facsimile machines built to 
TEMPEST security standards, reported second-quarter net income of $265,000 on 
sales of $5.4 million, up from a net loss of $508,000 on sales of $2 million in 
the like quarter one year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Net income for the six-month period ended March 31 was $22,000, contrasted with 
a net loss of $1.1 million for the like period the previous year. Sales for the 
two quarters were $9.4 million, about a 170% increase over sales of $3.5 
million for the corresponding period the previous year. 
</P>
