<P>
MAN'S BODY FOUND IN SANTIAGO CANYON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Sheriff's Department reported late Wednesday that the body of a fully 
clothed man was discovered near Modjeska Canyon Road and Santiago Canyon Road 
in Santiago Canyon, and investigators were treating the case as a probable 
homicide. 
</P>
<P>
A sheriff's spokesman said there was "evidence of trauma" to the body. The name 
of the dead man was being withheld until his family could be notified. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses reported seeing nearly a dozen police vehicles around the scene late 
Wednesday night. 
</P>
