<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROCEEDS FROM ALL-STAR WORKOUT WILL BENEFIT YOUTH TEAMS, FIELDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Sports Hall of Fame has been picked as the major charity 
recipient of the All-Star baseball game workout July 10 at Anaheim Stadium, the 
hall of fame announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds from the workout, the day before the All-Star Game at Anaheim Stadium, 
will go to a variety of youth groups in Southern California. A large amount of 
the money will go for the refurbishing Little League fields. 
</P>
<P>
Admission to the workout, which features a home-run hitting contest, is $5. 
There also will be a relay-throw competition and catcher's throw for accuracy 
during the workout. Tickets for the workout are on sale at Anaheim Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Any youth group interested in equipment donations or field renovation can write 
to the Orange County Sports Hall of Fame at 195 South C Street, Suite 250, 
Tustin, Calif. 92680. 
</P>
</TEXT>
