<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newport Pharmaceuticals International Inc. of Newport Beach reported net income 
of $267,000 for the first quarter, including a one-time gain of $165,000 from 
the repurchase of company debt securities. The results also reflect a reduction 
in the company's research and development spending following completion of 
clinical trials on the drug Isoprinosine. The company had a loss of $190,000 in 
the same quarter last year. Revenue for the 3-month period was $9.5 million, 
compared with $8.5 million a year ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA042789-0172 </DOCNO>
