<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARITY SCORECARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Celebrity Golf Tournament held at the Santa Ana Country Club on April 17 
raised an estimated $15,000 for the Discovery Museum of Orange County. Ken 
Forsche was chairman. 
</P>
<P>
The golf tournament held at the El Niguel Country Club in Laguna Niguel on 
April 17 netted an estimated $30,000 for CSP Youth Shelter. Thomas Green was 
chairman. 
</P>
<P>
The "Oooh La La! Au Bon Temps" dinner dance held at the Le Meridien Hotel in 
Newport Beach on Saturday raised an estimated $60,000 for the Sound of Music 
chapter of the Guilds of the Orange County Performings Arts Center. Sandra 
Beigel and Linda Smith were co-chairwomen. 
</P>
<P>
The "Night Aboard Sea Goddess" dinner and auction held at the Irvine Hilton 
&amp; Towers on Saturday raised an estimated $50,000 for the Orange County 
chapter of the National Multiple Sclerosis Society. Warren Johnson was 
chairman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Master Chorale director William Hall, left, enjoys a moment with 
Kathleen and John Rhynerson at " 'S Wonderful IV!" dinner/auction at Red Lion 
Inn in Costa Mesa on Sunday. JOHN FUNG / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
