<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
HEARING ON TRAFFIC PLANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Community Redevelopment Agency will hold a public hearing 
Wednesday on proposals to manage traffic in Hollywood and revitalize Hollywood 
Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
The Board of Commissioners will hear testimony on drafts of the Hollywood 
Transportation Plan and the Hollywood Boulevard District Urban Design Plan. 
Both proposals are elements of the broader Hollywood Redevelopment Plan, which 
was adopted in 1986 for an 1,100-acre section of central Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
The transportation plan will attempt to manage traffic and congestion problems 
over the next 20 years, while the Hollywood Boulevard plan will establish 
development guidelines for that thoroughfare. After they have been reviewed by 
the commissioners, they will be forwarded to the city's Planning Commission and 
the City Council for adoption. 
</P>
<P>
The hearing will be held at 9 a.m. in the Redevelopment Agency's fourth-floor 
board room, 354 S. Spring St., Los Angeles. The commissioners will accept 
written testimony until June 1. Comments may be mailed to the agency's 
Hollywood Project Office, 6255 Sunset Blvd., Suite 711, Hollywood, Calif. 
90028. 
</P>
