<P>
DRUGS FOUND IN HOFFMAN'S HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DOYLESTOWN, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Small quantities of illegal drugs were found in the home of Abbie Hoffman, the 
Yippie movement co-founder who committed suicide earlier this month, 
authorities said today. 
</P>
<P>
The drugs were found in a box in Hoffman's refrigerator, Bucks County Dist. 
Atty. Alan M. Rubenstein said. The box contained 9.38 grams of marijuana, 0.31 
grams of hashish, a cocaine residue and trace amounts of LSD, amphetamines and 
psilocybin, Rubenstein said. 
</P>
<P>
Hoffman, 52, died April 12 of what coroner Thomas Rosko called a "massive 
overdose" of the sedative phenobarbital and large quantities of alcohol. 
</P>
