<P>
BANDITS CLEAN UP IN SOAP PLANT RAID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANZIO, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Twenty bandits armed with pistols and machine guns raided a Colgate Palmolive 
factory today and escaped with $740,000 worth of soap, toothpaste, bubble bath 
and shampoo, police and company officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The bandits, who arrived with a dozen trucks to transport their loot, burst 
into the factory in this seaside city 35 miles south of Rome shortly after 
midnight, police said. They locked about 80 workers in a company truck and at 
gunpoint forced another 20 workers to load up the gang's trucks with the toilet 
articles. The gang then forced the rest of the workers into the company truck 
and drove off. 
</P>
